: `Profile.kt renders a static circular avatar from `R.drawable.ic_profile` plus an inert edit affordance, but it does not open a bitmap viewer, gallery preview, zoom surface, or EXIF/media metadata flow.`; `Profile.kt owns the profile navigation surface: the top-left back icon calls `navController.navigateUp()`, the logout button dispatches `ProfileEvent.PerformLogout`, and the logout callback navigates to onboarding while clearing the stack back to the graph...`; `Profile.kt keeps most profile content static, but it propagates UI actions through `ProfileViewModel.onEvent(ProfileEvent.PerformLogout)` and callback lambdas so logout navigation happens only after the view-model layer processes the event.`; `Profile.kt renders static profile content, placeholder card actions, and logout navigation only; it does not request runtime permissions, handle permission callbacks, or access protected platform APIs.`; `ProfileViewModel.onEvent` handles `ProfileEvent.PerformLogout` by launching a coroutine, toggling persisted login state through `LoginRepository`, and only then invoking the supplied callback so navigation happens after session mutation.`; `ProfileViewModel.kt contains only logout-event handling through `repository.toggleLoginState()` and a completion callback; it does not request permissions, process permission results, or touch protected APIs.`; `ProfileViewModel.kt has no init block, resume/pause refresh path, teardown override, or other screen lifecycle ownership; the file only reacts to a logout event when invoked by the UI.`\n73: - risk hints: `critical/high behavior cannot close on build pass alone`\n74: - acceptance evidence: `Closed critical/high features must record sourceBehavior, targetBehavior, parityLevel, targetEndpoints, and verificationEvidence.`; `Build pass alone is not per-feature verification.`\n75: \n76: ### `phase-03-onboarding-login-profile-verification-phase-tests-and-evidence` Verification and evidence policy\n77: \n78: - priority/type: `