{"type":"text","timestamp":1782389029030,"sessionID":"ses_1015ca6cfffeteaDphZUZFsMdV","part":{"id":"prt_efea9cf90001P7vE7vJ5E05ns5","messageID":"msg_efea9b195001T2F7UYj3KPq28k","sessionID":"ses_1015ca6cfffeteaDphZUZFsMdV","type":"text","text":"Completed the batch scope for `phase-03-onboarding-login-profile` focused on `presentation/profile` plus verification/evidence updates.\n\nChanged files:\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/profile/profile_page.cj`: tightened profile presentation to better match source behavior with a dedicated back affordance and circular avatar styling while keeping edit/section actions inert placeholders.\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/profile/profile_store.cj`: kept profile logout/back route contract stable and compile-safe.\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie/cjpm.toml`: added `profile.build.combined` entry for the dedicated phase test package so the test harness progresses past the previous package-config blocker.\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json`: updated 10 current-batch phase-03 rows with corrected `targetBehavior`/`verificationEvidence`, especially replacing stale “test passed” claims with the actual current harness blocker.\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.md`: synced from matrix authority patch.\n\nCommands run:\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\.cangjie-sdk\\6.1\\cangjie\\build-tools\\tools\\bin\\cjpm.exe test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` from `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie` with the report’s env overlay\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py --kind matrix --authority D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.json --patch D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\phase03-matrix-patch.json --markdown D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.md --plan-json D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\plan.json --target-project D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe .agents\\skills\\harmonyos-build\\build.py --project-root D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n\nBuild result:\n- PASS: `translation-inputs/build-reports/phase-03-onboarding-login-profile/build-report.md`\n- Focused test reproduction: FAIL, but the blocker moved forward from package config to SDK/link stage. The current bounded reproduction now fails on missing linker/sysroot artifacts `Scrt1.o`, `crti.o`, `crtn.o`, `-lm`, and `-lc` after the `profile.build.combined` fix.\n\nPlan changes:\n- none\n\nDeferred issues:\n- Target test harness for current phase is still blocked at SDK/link level after the local safe fix. Evidence recorded in current-batch matrix rows points to `translation-inputs/test-build-reports/phase-03-onboarding-login-profile/test-build-report.md` plus the bounded manual reproduction. No platform-capability rows needed updates for this batch.\n- I did not touch unrelated phase groups even though the matrix contains broader phase-03 entries.\n\nNotable outcomes:\n- `profile` route still preserves source-visible behavior: static avatar, inert edit affordance, back action, static section cards, logout after persisted session mutation.\n- Evidence is now internally consistent for this batch: rows no longer claim passing tests where the accepted test report says `TEST_COMPILE_FAIL`.\n- The local test-package config fix is useful for later batches too because it exposes the real environment blocker instead of failing immediately on missing `profile.build.combined`.\n\nNext recommended action:\n1. Fix the phase test harness environment/sysroot mismatch so `entry/src/test/cangjie` can link for `aarch64-linux-ohos`, then rerun the phase-03 test gate and upgrade the current evidence from blocker-based to passing test evidence.","time":{"start":1782389002128,"end":1782389029026}}}
